<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0, viewport-fit=cover">

  <title>Delete your account — Aquiplex</title>
  <meta name="description" content="How to permanently delete your Aquiplex account and Aqua AI data, what gets deleted, what is retained, and how to reach support if you cannot sign in.">
  <meta name="author" content="Aquiplex">

  <meta property="og:title" content="Delete your Aquiplex account">
  <meta property="og:description" content="Delete your account and all associated data from inside the app, or request deletion by email.">
  <meta property="og:url" content="https://aquiplex.com/delete-account">
  <meta property="og:type" content="website">

  <link rel="icon" href="/logo/favicon.ico" sizes="any">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;450;500;550;600;700&family=Newsreader:opsz,wght@6..72,400;6..72,500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/platform.css">
</head>
<body class="px-page">

  <%- include("partials/nav") %>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="px-page-hero center">
    <div class="px-container">
      <div class="px-eyebrow">Account &amp; data</div>
      <h1>Delete your account</h1>
      <p>You can permanently delete your Aquiplex account — and everything Aqua has stored for you — at any time, from inside the app. This page explains exactly how, and exactly what happens.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="px-waterline" aria-hidden="true">

  <!-- How to delete -->
  <section class="px-section">
    <div class="px-container">
      <div class="px-sec-head px-reveal">
        <div class="px-eyebrow">How to delete your account</div>
        <h2>Three steps, inside the app.</h2>
        <p>The same steps work in the Aquiplex Android app and on the web — it is the same account either way.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="px-steps">
        <div class="px-step px-reveal">
          <span class="px-step-num">Step 1</span>
          <h3>Open Settings</h3>
          <p>Sign in, open Aqua, then open <strong>Settings</strong> from the sidebar and select the <strong>Account</strong> tab.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="px-step px-reveal">
          <span class="px-step-num">Step 2</span>
          <h3>Choose Delete account</h3>
          <p>Under <strong>Danger zone</strong>, choose <strong>Delete account</strong>. You will be shown exactly what is about to be removed and asked to confirm.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="px-step px-reveal">
          <span class="px-step-num">Step 3</span>
          <h3>Confirm it's you</h3>
          <p>Enter your password, or — if you signed up with Google — confirm through Google. Deletion runs immediately and you are signed out on every device.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="px-btn-row center px-mt-lg">
        <a href="/aqua" class="px-btn px-btn-primary px-btn-lg">Open Aqua and delete my account</a>
        <a href="/login" class="px-btn px-btn-secondary px-btn-lg">Log in first</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="px-waterline" aria-hidden="true">

  <!-- What is deleted -->
  <section class="px-section">
    <div class="px-container">
      <div class="px-sec-head px-reveal">
        <div class="px-eyebrow">What gets deleted</div>
        <h2>Everything tied to your account. Permanently.</h2>
        <p>Deletion is immediate and irreversible. There is no recovery window, no archive, and no restore — once it completes, we cannot bring any of it back.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="px-list px-reveal">
        <div class="px-list-row">
          <div class="px-list-title">Your account</div>
          <div class="px-list-sub">Your login, email address, profile details, referral code, and credit wallet balance.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="px-list-row">
          <div class="px-list-title">Chats and conversations</div>
          <div class="px-list-sub">Every conversation, message, and title — including conversations you had already deleted, which are removed from our short-term backup snapshot as well.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="px-list-row">
          <div class="px-list-title">Memories</div>
          <div class="px-list-sub">Everything Aqua remembered about you: facts, beliefs, goals, relationships, episodes, and the derived intelligence built on top of them.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="px-list-row">
          <div class="px-list-title">Uploaded files and projects</div>
          <div class="px-list-sub">Uploaded documents, images, media, and code archives, along with everything extracted from them — parsed content, evidence, search indexes, and reasoning graphs.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="px-list-row">
          <div class="px-list-title">Generated artifacts</div>
          <div class="px-list-sub">Documents, presentations, spreadsheets, PDFs, and code projects Aqua created for you, deleted from storage along with their files.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="px-list-row">
          <div class="px-list-title">Sessions and sign-ins</div>
          <div class="px-list-sub">Every active session and token, on every device — you are signed out everywhere immediately.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="px-list-row">
          <div class="px-list-title">Purchase and credit history</div>
          <div class="px-list-sub">Your payment records and credit ledger entries held by Aquiplex.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="px-waterline" aria-hidden="true">

  <!-- What is retained -->
  <section class="px-section">
    <div class="px-container">
      <div class="px-sec-head px-reveal">
        <div class="px-eyebrow">What we retain</div>
        <h2>A short, deliberate list.</h2>
        <p>Nothing below identifies you or is linked to your account after deletion.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="px-list px-reveal">
        <div class="px-list-row">
          <div class="px-list-title">Anonymized billing event log</div>
          <div class="px-list-sub">We keep the payment-provider event records that make billing reliable — they stop a payment notification from being processed twice. Your account reference is removed from them, so they no longer point to you.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="px-list-row">
          <div class="px-list-title">Records held by our payment provider</div>
          <div class="px-list-sub">Razorpay keeps its own transaction records to meet financial and tax regulations. Those records sit with Razorpay, outside your Aquiplex account, and are governed by their retention obligations.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="px-list-row">
          <div class="px-list-title">Anonymous, aggregated statistics</div>
          <div class="px-list-sub">Counters used to keep the service reliable — such as how often a type of request succeeds. These are totals only: they contain no messages, no files, and no identifiers.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="px-list-row">
          <div class="px-list-title">Anything you published publicly</div>
          <div class="px-list-sub">Public submissions you made to the (retired) tools directory stay listed, with your account reference removed, because they describe third-party tools rather than you.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="px-waterline" aria-hidden="true">

  <!-- Locked out -->
  <section class="px-section">
    <div class="px-container px-narrow">
      <div class="px-sec-head px-reveal">
        <div class="px-eyebrow">If you can't sign in</div>
        <h2>Email us and we'll delete it for you.</h2>
        <p>
          If you have lost access to your account, email
          <strong>support@aquiplex.ai</strong> from the email address you signed up with,
          with the subject <strong>“Delete my account”</strong>. We will verify ownership,
          delete the account and all associated data, and confirm by reply — normally within
          7 days, and always within 30 days.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="px-btn-row center">
        <a href="mailto:support@aquiplex.ai?subject=Delete%20my%20account" class="px-btn px-btn-primary px-btn-lg">Email support@aquiplex.ai</a>
        <a href="/aqua/privacy" class="px-btn px-btn-secondary px-btn-lg">Read the Privacy Policy</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <%- include("partials/footer") %>

  <script>
    (function () {
      if (!('IntersectionObserver' in window)) {
        document.querySelectorAll('.px-reveal').forEach(function (el) { el.classList.add('in'); });
        return;
      }
      var io = new IntersectionObserver(function (entries) {
        entries.forEach(function (e) {
          if (e.isIntersecting) { e.target.classList.add('in'); io.unobserve(e.target); }
        });
      }, { threshold: 0.12 });
      document.querySelectorAll('.px-reveal').forEach(function (el) { io.observe(el); });
    })();
  </script>
</body>
</html>
